.TH "__nla_validate" 9 "__nla_validate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__nla_validate \- Validate a stream of attributes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __nla_validate
.BI "(const struct nlattr *head "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int maxtype "  ","
.BI "const struct nla_policy *policy "  ","
.BI "unsigned int validate "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack *extack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "head" 12
head of attribute stream
.IP "len" 12
length of attribute stream
.IP "maxtype" 12
maximum attribute type to be expected
.IP "policy" 12
validation policy
.IP "validate" 12
validation strictness
.IP "extack" 12
extended ACK report struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Validates all attributes in the specified attribute stream against the
specified policy. Validation depends on the validate flags passed, see
\fIenum netlink_validation\fP for more details on that.
See documenation of struct nla_policy for more details.

Returns 0 on success or a negative error code.
